TIER 2 -- complex shapes, no closed form, no ground truth
==========================================================================

PROVES:
  + six independently-built engines were run on the same op stream and
    their measured geometry (volume, bbox, genus, watertightness) did not
    disagree beyond each engine's physically-derived tolerance
  + the metamorphic laws held -- in particular scale_is_cubic, which
    relates two runs of the SAME engine and therefore holds even for an
    engine whose absolute numbers are all wrong
  + the solid that was WRITTEN TO DISK was re-measured by the output gate
    and was a closed, 2-manifold, positive-volume solid
  + an engine that REFUSED the plan said so, rather than building a
    different part quietly
DOES NOT PROVE:
  - that any part here is CORRECT -- there is no ground truth in this
    tier, by construction; that is the whole reason it can be pointed at a
    gyroid
  - that the engines are right -- they can SHARE a bug, and a consensus of
    five wrong answers is indistinguishable here from a consensus of five
    right ones
  - that the part matches any brief or intent -- the compared signature is
    MANY-TO-ONE, and a part with every hole bored in the wrong place
    matches every number in this report
  - that an op whose meaning is UNDERDETERMINED was implemented correctly
    -- six engines can agree because they share a reading of an ambiguous
    spec
  - anything at all about a feature finer than the coarsest engine's
    tessellation

